Access Control.description: The security access control endpoint in an AssociatedSecurityGroup relationship.

Activity Status.description: The current status of the subscription activity. Uses ActivityStatus enum.

Additional Properties.description: Additional user defined values organized as name value pairs in a dictionary.

Agreement End.description: The end date of the agreement as an ISO 8601 string.

Agreement Name.description: The name of the agreement to add an item to. Using qualified names is recommended.

Agreement Start.description: The start date of the agreement as an ISO 8601 string.

Anchor ID.description: Anchor identity for the collection. Typically a qualified name but if display name is unique then it could be used (not recommended)

Authors.description: Defines the authors if ab Authored Referenceable.

Business Imperatives.description: Defines the list of business imperatives the strategy supports.

Category.description: A user specified category name that can be used for example, to define product types or agreement types.

Certification Type.description: The license type being used for the license.

Class Word Classification.description: Classification from 0438. Applied to Referenceable. Marker classification (no attributes) indicating the element is a class word in a naming standard.

Confidence Classification.description: Classification from 0422. Structure: {status_identifier: int, confidence: int, steward: str, steward_type_name: str, steward_property_name: str, source: str, notes: str, level_identifier: int}. level_identifier uses ConfidenceLevel enum: UNCLASSIFIED=0, AD_HOC=1, TRANSACTIONAL=2, AUTHORITATIVE=3, DERIVED=4, OBSOLETE=5, OTHER=99.

Confidentiality Classification.description: Classification from 0422. Structure: {status_identifier: int, confidence: int, steward: str, steward_type_name: str, steward_property_name: str, source: str, notes: str, level_identifier: int}. level_identifier uses ConfidentialityLevel enum: UNCLASSIFIED=0, INTERNAL=1, CONFIDENTIAL=2, SENSITIVE=3, RESTRICTED=4, OTHER=99.

Content Status.description: The status of an AuthotredReferenceable. There is a list of valid values that this conforms to.

Criteria.description: The criteria for membership in a governance zone.

Criticality Classification.description: Classification from 0422. Structure: {status_identifier: int, confidence: int, steward: str, steward_type_name: str, steward_property_name: str, source: str, notes: str, level_identifier: int}. level_identifier uses CriticalityLevel enum: UNCLASSIFIED=0, MARGINAL=1, IMPORTANT=2, CRITICAL=3, CATASTROPHIC=4, OTHER=99.

Custodian.description: Custodian of the license or certification.

Data Collection End Time.description: End time for the data collection period.

Data Collection Start Time.description: Start time for the data collection period.

Deployed Implementation Type.description: The implementation type for a deploymed resource.

Description.description: Description of the contents of the definition or relationship.

Document Identifier.description: A user supplied identifier for the governance document.

Domain Identifier.description: String representing the governance domain. All domains is ALL

Effective From.description: A string in ISO-8601 format that defines the when an element becomes effective (visible).

Effective Time.description: An ISO-8601 string representing the time to use for evaluating effectivity of the elements related to this one.

Effective To.description: A string in ISO-8601 format that defines the when an element is no longer effective (visible).

End Date.description: Date at which the license or certification expires.

Entitlements.examples: Allowed to use within the organization.
Entitlements.description: A dictionary of property:value pairs describing entitlements.

Extended Properties.description: Additional user defined values organized as name value pairs in a dictionary.

External Source GUID.description: Identifier of an external source that is associated with this element.

External Source Name.description: Name of an external element that is associated with this element.

Glossary Term.description: Term that provides meaning to this field.

Impact Classification.description: Classification from 0422. Structure: {status_identifier: int, confidence: int, steward: str, steward_type_name: str, steward_property_name: str, source: str, notes: str, severity_identifier: int}. severity_identifier uses ImpactSeverity enum: UNCLASSIFIED=0, LOW=1, MEDIUM=2, HIGH=3, OTHER=99.

Implementation Description.description: Describes how this governance control is implemented.

Last Notification.description: The date of the last notification sent to this subscriber.

License Type.description: The license type being used for the license.

Link Label.description: Labels the link between two governance defninitions.

Max Height.description: Maximum height of the vertical scope.

Max Latitude.description: Maximum latitude of the geographic scope.

Max Longitude.description: Maximum longitude of the geographic scope.

Measurement.description: A measurement for a governance metric.

Merge Update.description: If true, only those attributes specified in the update will be updated; If false, any attributes not provided during the update will be set to None.

Min Height.description: Minimum height of the vertical scope.

Min Latitude.description: Minimum latitude of the geographic scope.

Min Longitude.description: Minimum longitude of the geographic scope.

Minimum Notification Interval.description: The minimum interval between notifications in milliseconds.

Modifier Classification.description: Classification from 0438. Applied to Referenceable. Marker classification (no attributes) indicating the element is a modifier in a naming standard.

Multiple Notifications Permitted.description: Whether multiple notifications are permitted for this notification type.

Name Patterns.description: Name patterns for naming standard rules.

Namespace.description: Optional namespace that scopes the field.

Next Scheduled Notification.description: The date of the next scheduled notification.

Notes.description: Notes about the license or certification.

Notification Count.description: The number of notifications sent so far.

Notification Interval.description: The interval between scheduled notifications in milliseconds.

Obligations.description: A dictionary of property:value pairs describing obligations.

Operation Name.description: The name of the operation controled by the SecurityAccessControl.

Parent at End1.description: Is the parent at end1 of the relationship?

Parent ID.description: Unique name of the parent element.

Parent Relationship Attributes.description: Optional  details of the parent relationship attributes.

Parent Relationship Type Name.description: The kind of the relationship to the parent element.

Planned Completion Date.description: The planned completion date for the notification type.

Planned Start Date.description: The planned start date for the notification type.

Policy.description: The governance policy endpoint in a GovernanceResponse or GovernanceMechanism relationship.

Policy Management Point.description: Combined classification from 0435. Applied to Referenceable. Structure: {point_type: str, name: str, description: str}. point_type is one of: PolicyAdministrationPoint, PolicyDecisionPoint, PolicyEnforcementPoint, PolicyInformationPoint, PolicyRetrievalPoint. A Referenceable may have multiple policy management point classifications simultaneously.

Prime Word Classification.description: Classification from 0438. Applied to Referenceable. Marker classification (no attributes) indicating the element is a prime word in a naming standard.

Qualified Name.description: A unique qualified name for the element. Generated using the qualified name pattern  if not user specified.

Rationale.description: The rationale for using this control to  support this policy.

Referenceable.description: The object being licensed or certified.

Regulation Source.description: The source of the regulation - often, an authority.

Restrictions.description: A dictionary of property:value pairs describing restrictions.

Retention Classification.description: Classification from 0422. Structure: {status_identifier: int, confidence: int, steward: str, steward_type_name: str, steward_property_name: str, source: str, notes: str, basis_identifier: int, associated_guid: str, archive_after: date, delete_after: date}. basis_identifier uses RetentionBasis enum: UNCLASSIFIED=0, TEMPORARY=1, PROJECT_LIFETIME=2, TEAM_LIFETIME=3, CONTRACT_LIFETIME=4, REGULATED_LIFETIME=5, TIMEBOXED_LIFETIME=6, OTHER=99.

Scope Elements.description: Map of element identifiers defining the scope of the data lens.

Search Keywords.description: Keywords to facilitate finding the element

Security Group.description: The security group endpoint in an AssociatedSecurityGroup relationship.

Security Tags.description: Classification from 0423. Applied to Referenceable. Structure: {security_labels: list[str], security_properties: dict[str, object], access_groups: dict[str, list[str]]}.

Start Date.description: Date at which the license or certification takes effect.

Status.description: The status of the business imperative. There is a list of valid values that this conforms to.

Supports Policies.existing_element: Policies - Governance Principles; Governance Obligations; Governance Approaches
Supports Policies.description: The policies that this governance control supports.

Usage.description: How the governance definition will be used.

Usage Measurements.description: A dictionary of property:value pairs describing usage measurements.

User Defined Content Status.description: Only valid if Content Status is set to OTHER. User defined & managed status values.

User Defined Status.description: Only valid if Product Status is set to OTHER. User defined & managed status values.

Zone Membership.description: Classification from 0424. Applied to OpenMetadataRoot. Structure: {zone_membership: list[str]}. Lists the governance zones an element belongs to.

Sources.description: A map of source strings (e.g. URL, DOI, ISBN).

License.description: The license associated with the external reference.

Copyright.description: The copyright associated with the external reference.

Attribution.description: Attribution string to describe the external reference.

Media Type.description: Type of media (e.g. image, audio, video, document).

Media Type Other Id.description: An id associated with the media type when not using a standard valid value.

Default Media Usage.description: How the media is being used by default.

Default Media Usage Other Id.description: An id associated with the default media usage when not using a standard valid value.

Number of Pages.description: The number of pages in the document.

Publication Series.description: The series this publication is part of.

Publication Series Volume.description: The volume in the series that contains the citation.

First Publication Date.description: Date of first publication in ISO 8601 format (e.g. 2025-01-31).

Publication Numbers.description: Identification numbers of the publication (ISBN, ISSN, DOI, etc.).

Element Name.description: A referenceable to link to the external reference.

External Reference.description: The external reference to link to.

Media Reference.description: The related media reference to link to.

Cited Document.description: The cited document to link to.

Label.description: Labels the link between the referenceable and the external reference.

Media Id.description: An identifier of the media being referenced.

Media Usage.description: How the media is being used in this specific link.

Media Usage Other Id.description: An id associated with the media usage when not using a standard valid value.

Reference Id.description: An identifier of the cited document in the link context.

Pages.description: The specific pages referenced in the cited document.

Create External Reference.description: Create or update an External Reference - a Referenceable that describes an external source of information.

Create External Data Source.description: Create or update an External Data Source - an external reference that refers to an external data source.

Create External Model Source.description: Create or update an External Model Source - an external reference that refers to an external analytical or AI model source.

Create Related Media.description: Create or update Related Media - an external reference to media such as images, audio, video or documents.

Create Cited Document.description: Create or update a Cited Document - an external reference to a published document with full bibliographic metadata.

Link External Reference.description: Link an external reference to a referenceable via the ExternalReferenceLink relationship.

Link Media Reference.description: Link a related media reference to a referenceable via the MediaReferenceLink relationship.

Link Cited Document.description: Link a cited document to a referenceable via the DocumentCitationLink relationship.

Create External Source Code.description: Create or update an External Source Code reference - an external reference that refers to software source code. If the component created from this source code is catalogued, it is linked to the ExternalSourceCode using the ExternalReferenceLink relationship.
